<!-- K3s INTEGRATION EVALUATION (Grok's Recommendations)                        -->
<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<div style="background-color: #e3f2fd; border: 2px solid #1976d2; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h3 style="color: #0d47a1; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">✅ K3s Strategy Evaluation & Integration (2025-12-24)</h3>
    
    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Grok's K3s Plan Assessment</h4>
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.6;">
        <li>✅ <strong>Stability Focus</strong> - K3s master placement on proxmox720 (stable Dell R720 hardware) reduces infrastructure risk</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Zero-Downtime Migration</strong> - Master-slave replication + Galera clustering for seamless cutover from bare-metal 192.168.1.198</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Clear Node Placement Strategy</strong> - Distributed workers across proxmox720/proxmoxws/proxmoxt210 with explicit VM ID mappings</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Rollback Procedures</strong> - Documented DNS revert and 3-day bare-metal retention for safe cutover</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Homelab-Ready</strong> - K3s chosen over full Kubernetes (lower resource overhead, simpler management)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Integration Points with Existing Strategy:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.6;">
        <li>✅ <strong>Phase 1-2 Unchanged</strong> - Docker Compose remains for dev/staging environments (lower overhead, quicker iteration)</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Phase 3: K3s Cluster Rebuild</strong> - Replace previous K3s nodes with stable topology per Grok plan</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Phase 4: Galera StatefulSet</strong> - Deploy MariaDB Galera in K3s for production database HA</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Phase 5: Zero-Downtime Migration</strong> - Replication-based cutover from bare-metal → K3s</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Phase 6: Application Cutover</strong> - DNS/config switch with rollback capability</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Recommended Adjustments to Grok's Plan:</strong></p>
    <div style="background-color: #fff9c4; border-left: 4px solid #f57f17; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.8;">
            <li><strong>Pre-Cluster Preparation</strong> - Complete Docker Compose phases first to validate environment variables, volume mounts, and network configs (reduces K3s surprises)</li>
            <li><strong>MetalLB IP Pool</strong> - Define LoadBalancer pool from available LAN IPs (e.g., 192.168.1.200-250) BEFORE deploying services</li>
            <li><strong>Persistent Storage Strategy</strong> - Choose between NFS (simpler), Longhorn (K3s-native), or Proxmox PVE storage before Phase 3</li>
            <li><strong>Monitoring/Observability</strong> - Add Prometheus + Grafana from day 1 for cluster health visibility (critical for homelab stability)</li>
            <li><strong>Backup Automation</strong> - Implement automated K3s cluster backups before production migration (Grok plan doesn't cover this)</li>
            <li><strong>Network Redundancy</strong> - Consider dual-node master setup on proxmox720 if hardware supports (improves HA beyond Grok's single master)</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Timeline Impact:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
        <li>Phases 1-2 (Docker Compose): <strong>1-2 months</strong> (unchanged)</li>
        <li>Phase 3 (K3s Rebuild on stable hosts): <strong>1 week</strong> (per Grok, faster than building from scratch)</li>
        <li>Phase 4-5 (Galera + migration): <strong>1-2 weeks</strong> (replication validation required)</li>
        <li>Phase 6 (Cutover + stabilization): <strong>1 week</strong> (3-day rollback window)</li>
        <li><strong>Total: 3-4 months</strong> (vs. original 4-6 months due to K3s clarity)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p style="color: #0d47a1; font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Approval Status</strong>: Grok's K3s plan APPROVED for integration into Phase 3+. Maintain Docker Compose phases for dev/staging continuity.</p>
</div>

<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<!-- CRITICAL DIAGNOSTIC: Docker MySQL Connectivity Issue (2025-11-19)        -->
<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border: 2px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h3 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">🔴 CRITICAL: Docker Containers Cannot Connect to Production MySQL</h3>
    
    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Current Situation (Updated Dec 2, 2025)</h4>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.6;">
        <li><strong>Port 3001</strong>: ✅ <strong>WORKING</strong> - Returns HTML content (native Perl process running locally on host)</li>
        <li><strong>Port 3000</strong>: ✅ <strong>CONTAINER RUNNING</strong> - Docker dev container responds with HTTP 200 (database connectivity configured via network_mode: host in docker-compose.dev.yml line 9)</li>
        <li><strong>Port 5000</strong>: ⚠️ <strong>CONTAINER RUNS BUT NEEDS FIX</strong> - Docker prod container responds with HTTP 200 BUT docker-compose.prod.yml has conflicting network configuration (network_mode: host at line 9 conflicts with networks: at line 46 - this is invalid in Docker v2)</li>
        <li><strong>Production MySQL</strong>: ✅ <strong>REACHABLE VIA HOST NETWORK MODE</strong> - Using network_mode: host allows containers to access 192.168.1.198:3306 directly. See "Database Connection Setup & Container Startup" section for complete setup instructions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Root Cause Analysis</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Issue</strong>: Docker containers are isolated on their own internal network (172.20.0.0/16) and cannot route packets to the host network (192.168.0.0/16).</p>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Network Architecture</strong>:</p>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>Host Network</strong>: 192.168.x.x (where production MySQL lives at 192.168.1.198:3306)</li>
            <li><strong>Docker Network</strong>: 172.20.0.0/16 bridge (where containers live at 172.20.0.2, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>Container DNS Resolution</strong>: Resolves "database" to 172.20.0.3 (local Docker service), NOT to external hosts</li>
            <li><strong>Firewall/Routing</strong>: Docker daemon does not expose host network routes to containers by default</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Why Port 3001 Works</strong>: The native Perl process via `perl script/comserv_server.pl -p3001` runs directly on the host OS. It can access the host network and reach 192.168.1.198 because it's not isolated like Docker containers.</p>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Configuration Mismatch</h4>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Component</strong></th>
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Configured For</strong></th>
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Actually Using</strong></th>
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Status</strong></th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">docker-compose.yml</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Production MySQL at 192.168.1.198</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Hardcoded credentials (SECURITY RISK)</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">❌ EXPOSED</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Running Docker env vars</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">COMSERV_DB_LOCAL_ENCY_HOST=192.168.1.198</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">database (localhost via Docker DNS)</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ OVERRIDE</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">db_config.json (mounted)</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Production 192.168.1.198 + ZeroTier IPs</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Not used (env vars take priority)</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;">⚠️ IGNORED</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font);">What Changed to Get Ports 3000/5000 Returning Content</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Key Commit</strong>: <code>03b76bd5</code> - "Update Docker development setup and enhance Kubernetes migration documentation"</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Change</strong>: docker-compose.yml was modified to:</p>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Mount code volumes (lib/, script/, root/, config/, t/)</li>
            <li>Configure Starman servers via Supervisor in containers</li>
            <li>Set healthcheck endpoints to verify port responsiveness</li>
            <li>Configure Redis for session caching (optional)</li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Result</strong>: Containers now start successfully and respond to HTTP requests on ports 3000/5000, but the application cannot access the production MySQL database because of network isolation.</p>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font);">Why Docker Still Can't Connect to Production MySQL</h4>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Factor</strong></th>
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Details</strong></th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Network Isolation</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Docker bridge network (172.20.0.0/16) does not include routes to host network (192.168.0.0/16). Container routing table only knows about Docker internal addresses.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>DNS Resolution</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Docker-internal DNS (127.0.0.11:53) resolves all hostnames to Docker services only. External hosts like 192.168.1.198 are not resolvable unless Docker daemon has host network access configured.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Firewall Rules</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Even if routing existed, Linux iptables rules may block traffic. Docker's default FORWARD chain policies restrict inter-network communication.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>MySQL Service Binding</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Production MySQL at 192.168.1.198 may only be listening on eth0 (host network interface). It doesn't know about the Docker bridge network, so it cannot route return traffic.</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">⚠️ CRITICAL FIX REQUIRED: docker-compose.prod.yml Network Conflict</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #ffebee; border: 2px solid #d32f2f; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Issue</strong>: The file <code>docker-compose.prod.yml</code> has BOTH <code>network_mode: host</code> (line 9) AND <code>networks:</code> section (line 46-47). This is invalid in Docker Compose v2 and will cause errors.</p>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Fix</strong>: Remove the <code>networks:</code> section from the web-prod service and all references to comserv-network. The network_mode: host is the correct solution for database connectivity.</p>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Commands to fix:</strong></p>
        <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Option 1: Edit docker-compose.prod.yml and remove lines 46-47:
#   networks:
#     - comserv-network

# Option 2: Comment out the networks section:
# networks:
#   comserv-network:
#     driver: bridge

# After fixing, verify with:
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml config
</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">⚠️ STRATEGIC PIVOT: Why Docker Compose is NOT the Long-Term Solution</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #ffebee; border: 2px solid #d32f2f; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 0;"><strong>The Fundamental Problem:</strong> Docker Compose cannot simultaneously support:</p>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 10px;">
            <li><strong>Port mapping (published ports)</strong> - Requires bridge network mode ✅ but blocks external DB access ❌</li>
            <li><strong>External database connectivity</strong> - Requires host network mode ✅ but port mappings are ignored ❌</li>
        </ol>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Attempted Solutions & Their Limits:</strong></p>
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Solution</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Port Access</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">External DB</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Production Ready</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">network_mode: host</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">❌ Disabled</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">❌ No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Bridge + custom routing</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;">⚠️ Complex</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;">⚠️ Fragile</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">macvlan driver</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;">⚠️ OS-dependent</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Kubernetes</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Works</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #4caf50;">✅ Yes</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Decision (Dec 20, 2025):</strong> Invest effort in Kubernetes readiness instead of working around Docker's fundamental networking limitations. K8s provides:</p>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>✅ Native multi-network support (services can reach both internal and external DBs)</li>
            <li>✅ Kubernetes Secrets for credential management (aligned with CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt)</li>
            <li>✅ Service discovery without hardcoded IPs</li>
            <li>✅ Rolling updates, health checks, and auto-recovery</li>
            <li>✅ Production-ready security model (network policies, RBAC)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: #4caf50; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">✅ REVISED Approach: Prepare for Kubernetes Migration (Primary Focus)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; border: 1px solid #4caf50; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.8;">
            <li><strong>Phase 0 (Immediate): Make Application K8s-Ready</strong>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 5px;">
                    <li>✅ Ensure all configuration comes from environment variables (not hardcoded paths)</li>
                    <li>✅ Implement graceful shutdown handlers (SIGTERM, readiness probes)</li>
                    <li>✅ Remove Docker Compose network_mode dependencies (use standard bridge networks)</li>
                    <li>✅ Create database initialization script that works in any environment</li>
                    <li>✅ Document credential injection mechanism (env vars → database credentials)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Phase 1 (Weeks 1-2): Kubernetes Cluster Setup</strong>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 5px;">
                    <li>Install local K8s (minikube) for development testing</li>
                    <li>Create Kubernetes manifests (Deployment, Service, ConfigMap, Secret)</li>
                    <li>Write helm charts for application deployment</li>
                    <li>Define network policies (allow external DB access, restrict inter-pod traffic)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Phase 2 (Weeks 2-3): Credential Integration with K8s Secrets</strong>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 5px;">
                    <li>Move database credentials to K8s Secrets (remove from .env files)</li>
                    <li>Align with CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt Phase 1+ implementations</li>
                    <li>Test credential rotation without downtime</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div> privileges and more complex networking config</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Best-practice (Long-term Production - 4-6 hours)</strong>: Use Zerotier or Tailscale
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 5px;">
                    <li>Install Zerotier or Tailscale client in Docker containers (add to Dockerfile)</li>
                    <li>Database server joins same Zerotier/Tailscale network (already joined)</li>
                    <li>Containers resolve database via virtual IP (e.g., 10.147.1.100 or 100.64.x.x)</li>
                    <li>Works for local, on-site, and off-site scenarios without exposing host network</li>
                    <li>More secure than host networking, enables future multi-cloud deployments</li>
                    <li>Recommended for Kubernetes Phase 6-7</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

    <h4 style="color: #ff6f00; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Detailed Technical Analysis (Updated Nov 22, 2025)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #fff8e1; border: 1px solid #ff6f00; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Root Cause Breakdown</strong>: The issue is multi-faceted. It's not just one problem but a combination of six interconnected issues:</p>
        
        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">1. Network Isolation (PRIMARY CAUSE)</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Docker bridge network (172.20.0.0/16) does not route to host network (192.168.x.x)</li>
            <li><strong>Impact</strong>: Containers cannot send packets to 192.168.1.198:3306</li>
            <li><strong>Symptom</strong>: DBI returns error code 2002 (Connection refused) or connection timeout</li>
            <li><strong>Code Location</strong>: RemoteDB.pm lines 69-77 (config loading) cannot help because network routing prevents connection</li>
            <li><strong>Verification Command</strong>: Inside container: <code>route -n | grep 192.168</code> returns nothing (no route exists)</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">2. DNS Resolution Failure</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Problem</strong>: Docker internal DNS (127.0.0.11:53) only knows Docker service names, not external IP addresses</li>
            <li><strong>Impact</strong>: Even if app resolves "database" as hostname, it gets Docker service IP, not 192.168.1.198</li>
            <li><strong>Verification Command</strong>: Inside container: <code>cat /etc/resolv.conf</code> shows <code>nameserver 127.0.0.11</code> (Docker's DNS)</li>
            <li><strong>Limitation</strong>: Cannot resolve external private network hosts without special configuration</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">3. Configuration Priority System (SECONDARY CAUSE)</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Location</strong>: Comserv/Model/RemoteDB.pm, lines 50-100 (_load_config method)</li>
            <li><strong>Priority Order</strong>:
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0 5px 20px;">
                    <li>K8s Secrets at /var/run/secrets/dbi (not available in docker-compose)</li>
                    <li>Environment variables (COMSERV_DB_* or COMSERV_ALLOW_LOCALHOST_OVERRIDE)</li>
                    <li>/opt/comserv/db_config.json (exists but may be readonly)</li>
                    <li>$ENV{COMSERV_DB_CONFIG} path (not set by default)</li>
                    <li>Relative path from FindBin (doesn't exist in container)</li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Security Risk</strong>: docker-compose.prod.yml lines 15-21 expose DB credentials directly in YAML file</li>
            <li><strong>Missing Validation</strong>: No health check confirms database connectivity during startup</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">4. Port Binding vs. Network Connectivity Confusion</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Key Distinction</strong>: HTTP ports (3000, 5000) use port mapping; database requires network routing</li>
            <li><strong>Why Ports 3000/5000 Work</strong>:
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0 5px 20px;">
                    <li>docker-compose: <code>ports: ["3000:3000"]</code> means traffic on host:3000 → container:3000</li>
                    <li>User runs <code>curl http://localhost:3000</code> and gets HTTP 200 (port mapping works)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Why 3306 Can't Work This Way</strong>:
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0 5px 20px;">
                    <li>MySQL port is NOT published from container (would be security risk)</li>
                    <li>Container needs to initiate connection to external 192.168.1.198:3306 (outbound, not inbound)</li>
                    <li>This requires network routing and firewall rules, not port mapping</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Common Misconception</strong>: Users might think "just publish the database port" would work; it won't without network access</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">5. Hardcoded Environment Variables Without Host Network</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>File</strong>: docker-compose.prod.yml, lines 15-21</li>
            <li><strong>Configuration</strong>:
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 5px; margin: 5px 0; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.4;">DB_HOST: ${DB_HOST_PROD:-192.168.1.198}
DB_PORT: ${DB_PORT_PROD:-3306}
DB_USER: ${DB_USER_PROD:-shanta_forager}
DB_PASS: ${DB_PASS_PROD:-UA=nPF8*m+T#}</pre>
            </li>
            <li><strong>The Problem</strong>: These variables are theoretically correct but network isolation prevents their use</li>
            <li><strong>Security Issue</strong>: Database credentials visible in plain text in YAML file (should use K8s Secrets or GitHub encrypted secrets)
                <br /><strong style="color: #1976d2;">→ See <a href="/diagnostic/credentials" style="color: var(--link-color); text-decoration: underline;">CREDENTIALS_AUDIT_AND_PLAN.tt</a> for comprehensive credential management strategy</strong>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Impact</strong>: If someone gains access to docker-compose files, they have full database credentials</li>
        </ul>

        <h5 style="color: #d84315; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">6. Container-to-Host Networking Configuration Missing</h5>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Missing Configuration</strong>: No <code>network_mode: host</code> or custom bridge defined in docker-compose</li>
            <li><strong>Files Affected</strong>:
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0 5px 20px;">
                    <li>docker-compose.yml (dev) - lines 1-50</li>
                    <li>docker-compose.dev.yml - lines 1-50</li>
                    <li>docker-compose.prod.yml - lines 1-50</li>
                    <li>Dockerfile - no networking diagnostics during build</li>
                    <li>docker-entrypoint.sh - no network validation before app startup</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Missing Diagnostics</strong>:
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0 5px 20px;">
                    <li>No check for routing to 192.168.0.0/16 during container startup</li>
                    <li>No DNS resolution test for database hostname</li>
                    <li>No attempt to connect to database before app starts serving requests</li>
                    <li>No container inspection of networking configuration</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h4 style="color: #ff6f00; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Why Host-Based Port 3001 Works (Reference)</h4>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
            <li><strong>Command</strong>: <code>perl /opt/comserv/script/comserv_server.pl -p3001</code></li>
            <li><strong>Process Model</strong>: Runs directly on host OS kernel, not containerized</li>
            <li><strong>Network Access</strong>: Has full access to host's routing table and network interfaces (eth0, eth1, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>Connection Flow</strong>: Host network stack → 192.168.1.198:3306 via direct kernel socket (no Docker DNS translation)</li>
            <li><strong>No Isolation</strong>: Can read host files, see all processes, access all network routes</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 style="color: #ff6f00; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Critical Files to Review and Fix</h4>
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>File</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Issue</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Action</strong></th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>RemoteDB.pm:50-100</code></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Config loading assumes connectivity exists</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Add network diagnostics, graceful fallback</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker-compose.prod.yml:15-21</code></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Credentials in plain text (SECURITY RISK)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Migrate to K8s Secrets or GitHub encrypted env</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker-entrypoint.sh</code></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No network validation before app startup</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Add connectivity checks, warn on failure</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>Dockerfile</code></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No networking strategy documented</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Add Zerotier/Tailscale for remote access (Phase 6+)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker-compose.*.yml</code></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No network mode or bridge configuration</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Add <code>network_mode: host</code> for dev, bridge config for prod</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <h4 style="color: #ff6f00; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Verification Commands (Diagnose From Container)</h4>
        <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Check container routing table (should show 192.168.0.0/16)
docker exec &lt;container-id&gt; route -n

# Check DNS configuration
docker exec &lt;container-id&gt; cat /etc/resolv.conf

# Test DNS resolution
docker exec &lt;container-id&gt; nslookup 192.168.1.198

# Test network connectivity to database
docker exec &lt;container-id&gt; nc -zv 192.168.1.198 3306

# Check MySQL connectivity
docker exec &lt;container-id&gt; mysql -h 192.168.1.198 -u shanta_forager -p'UA=nPF8*m+T#' -e "SELECT 1;"

# View Perl DBI trace (in app logs)
docker logs &lt;container-id&gt; | grep -i "dbi\|connection\|error 2002"
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<!-- CRITICAL: Database Connection Setup & Container Startup Instructions     -->
<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<div id="database-setup" style="background-color: #e8f5e9; border: 2px solid #4caf50; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h3 style="color: #2e7d32; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">✅ SOLUTION: Database Connection Setup & Container Startup (Docker v2)</h3>
    
    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h4>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.6;">
        <li><strong>Docker Compose v2</strong>: Verify with <code>docker compose version</code> (should show v2.x)</li>
        <li><strong>Database Accessible</strong>: Production MySQL at 192.168.1.198:3306 must be reachable from host</li>
        <li><strong>Credentials Available</strong>: DB_PASS environment variable or .env file configured</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 1: Configure Database Connection (5 minutes)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Option A: Using .env file (Recommended)</strong></p>
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Create .env file in project root
cat > .env << 'EOF'
# Development database
DB_HOST=192.168.1.198
DB_PORT=3306
DB_NAME=ency
DB_USER=shanta_forager
DB_PASS=your_actual_password_here

# Production database (for prod compose file)
DB_HOST_PROD=192.168.1.198
DB_PORT_PROD=3306
DB_NAME_PROD=ency
DB_USER_PROD=shanta_forager
DB_PASS_PROD=your_actual_password_here
EOF

# Secure the file
chmod 600 .env
</code></pre>

        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Option B: Using environment variables</strong></p>
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Export before running docker compose
export DB_PASS="your_actual_password_here"
export DB_PASS_PROD="your_actual_password_here"
</code></pre>
        
        <p style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT</strong>: Never commit .env file to git! It's already in .gitignore.</p>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 2: Build Container Images (First Time Only, ~5 minutes)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Note</strong>: Docker v2 uses <code>docker compose</code> (with space) not <code>docker-compose</code> (with hyphen)</p>
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Navigate to project directory
cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv

# Build development image
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml build

# Build production image
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build

# Verify images exist
docker images | grep comserv
</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 3: Start Containers (30 seconds)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Development Environment (Port 3000)</strong></p>
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Start in detached mode
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d

# View logs
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs -f

# Check status
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml ps

# Test connection
curl -I http://localhost:3000/health
</code></pre>

        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Production Environment (Port 5000)</strong></p>
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Start in detached mode
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d

# View logs
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml logs -f

# Check status
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml ps

# Test connection
curl -I http://localhost:5000/health
</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step 4: Verify Database Connectivity (1 minute)</h4>
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 5px 0;"><code># Get container name
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml ps

# Test database connection from inside container
docker exec -it comserv-web-dev bash -c "mysql -h \$DB_HOST -P \$DB_PORT -u \$DB_USER -p\$DB_PASS -e 'SELECT 1;'"

# Check application logs for database errors
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs | grep -i "dbi\|database\|connection"
</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Common Commands Reference</h4>
    <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Task</th>
            <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Command</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Stop containers</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Restart containers</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml restart</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Rebuild after code changes</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d --build</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">View real-time logs</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs -f</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Shell into container</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker exec -it comserv-web-dev bash</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Remove containers & volumes</td>
            <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down -v</code></td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4 style="color: #ff6f00; font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting</h4>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); line-height: 1.6;">
        <li><strong>Port already in use</strong>: Stop existing processes with <code>sudo lsof -i :3000</code> then <code>kill -9 &lt;PID&gt;</code></li>
        <li><strong>Database connection refused</strong>: Verify host can reach database: <code>mysql -h 192.168.1.198 -P 3306 -u shanta_forager -p</code></li>
        <li><strong>Container exits immediately</strong>: Check logs with <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs</code></li>
        <li><strong>Permission denied on .env</strong>: Ensure file permissions are correct: <code>chmod 600 .env</code></li>
        <li><strong>Network mode conflict</strong>: docker-compose.prod.yml has both network_mode and networks defined (lines 9 and 46) - this is invalid. Remove one.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Overview</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This document serves as a living blueprint for transitioning Comserv from manual server deployments to a fully containerized, Kubernetes-based infrastructure. The strategy spans 7 implementation phases over 4-6 months, with clear deliverables, pros/cons analysis, and decision points at each phase.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Deployment Model</strong>: Manual SSH + git pull + restart starman on production server. <strong>Target Model</strong>: Zero-downtime, auto-scaling Kubernetes cluster with CI/CD automation.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="current-state" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Current State Analysis</h2>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Existing Deployment Workflow</h3>
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>Developer Machines (Multiple)
↓ [git clone + local changes]GitHub Repository
    ↓ [git push from developer machine]
Production Server (On-Premises)
    ↓ [Manual: git pull + comserv_server.pl + restart starman]
Live Application
                </code></pre>
            </div>        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Current Pain Points</h3>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>Manual updates</strong>: Each deployment requires SSH access and manual steps</li>
            <li><strong>Environment inconsistency</strong>: Developer machine ≠ production server setup</li>
            <li><strong>No rollback mechanism</strong>: Failed updates require manual recovery</li>
            <li><strong>Scaling limitation</strong>: Adding servers means duplicating manual setup</li>
            <li><strong>Update downtime</strong>: Application down during comserv_server.pl execution</li>
            <li><strong>Port mapping issues</strong>: As discovered with Docker testing (port 5000/3000 confusion)</li>
            <li><strong>Database management</strong>: Manual synchronization across environments</li>
            <li><strong>Developer onboarding</strong>: New developers must set up entire Perl/MySQL stack locally</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Current Infrastructure</h3>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>Deployment Target</strong>: On-premises Proxmox with potential for additional physical servers</li>
            <li><strong>Application Runtime</strong>: Catalyst Perl framework via Starman server</li>
            <li><strong>Database</strong>: MySQL/PostgreSQL with future SQLite offline mode option</li>
            <li><strong>Version Control</strong>: Local git clone, manual push/pull workflow (only one developer currently)</li>
            <li><strong>CI/CD</strong>: None (manual everything)</li>
            <li><strong>Container Status</strong>: Docker container exists but not yet integrated with production workflow</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="target-state" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Target State Vision</h2>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">End Goal: Production-Ready Kubernetes</h3>
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>Developer Machines → Standardized Docker Dev Environment
↓GitHub Repository → Automated via CI/CD
    ↓
CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions) → Build, Test, Push to Registry
    ↓
Kubernetes Cluster (Multi-node on Proxmox)
    ├─ App Containers (Replicated, Auto-scaled)
    ├─ Database Service (Persistent)
    └─ Monitoring/Logging
    ↓
Live Application (Zero-Downtime Deployments)
                </code></pre>
            </div>        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Key Benefits When Achieved</h3>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li> <strong>Zero-downtime updates</strong> - Blue-green or rolling updates</li>
            <li> <strong>Automatic scaling</strong> - Handle load spikes automatically</li>
            <li> <strong>Consistency</strong> - Same environment from dev → prod</li>
            <li> <strong>Rollback capability</strong> - Revert to previous version instantly</li>
            <li> <strong>Multi-developer friendly</strong> - Standardized local environment</li>
            <li> <strong>Future cloud migration</strong> - K8s on Proxmox → Cloud K8s seamlessly</li>
            <li> <strong>Self-healing infrastructure</strong> - Failed containers restart automatically</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

