<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="decisions" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Decisions - TEAM CONSENSUS RECORDED</h2>

        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Container Registry</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Decision</strong>: GitHub Container Registry (GHCR)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Rationale</strong>: Already integrated with GitHub, free tier available, simplest implementation path</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">CI/CD Platform</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Decision</strong>: GitHub Actions</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Rationale</strong>: Already using GitHub for source control, minimal setup, cost-effective</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Database Strategy & DBI Management</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Decision</strong>: Separate database server (not containerized) for performance and persistence. Use Kubernetes Secrets for DBI (database connection info) storage in production/staging. For local dev, use secure .env files with placeholders.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Rationale</strong>: Secrets provide encryption at rest, RBAC access control, and integration with external managers. Avoids plaintext files like db_config.json in git or exposed envs.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Migration from db_config.json</strong>: All current systems use db_config.json as primary DBI source. On first container startup, import json contents to Kubernetes Secrets (via init container script), then delete the json file. For new/off-site computers without json:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Local Net Access</strong>: Use Zerotier virtual network for secure, VPN-like connectivity. Assign static virtual IPs (e.g., 10.147.x.x) to DB server and clients. Resolve hosts via Zerotier-managed DNS (e.g., db-server.zerotier.net resolves to virtual IP).</li>
                <li><strong>Off-Site Access</strong>: Zerotier clients auto-join the network on install. No port forwarding needed; traffic routes peer-to-peer. Fallback: Use Tailscale (similar mesh VPN) if Zerotier DNS latency is high.</li>
                <li><strong>Implementation</strong>: Zerotier Central dashboard for network management. Enable managed routes and DNS. Clients pull DBI from Secrets (dev) or json import (legacy).</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Backup Plan</strong>: Document current backups; adapt for Secrets rotation (e.g., kubectl create secret with new values).</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Developer/Git Workflow Notes</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Status</strong>: Single developer, no feature branches, all work to main branch</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Plan for Multiple Developers</strong>: Once additional developers join, will implement Git Flow with feature branches and pull request reviews</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Workflow</strong>: Straightforward - clone, edit, git push to main, CI/CD handles the rest</p>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<!-- IMPLEMENTATION: Docker Networking Fix                                     -->
<!-- ========================================================================== -->
<div style="background-color: #e3f2fd; border: 2px solid #1976d2; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; border-radius: 4px;">
    <h3 style="color: #1565c0; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">✅ IMMEDIATE ACTION: Enable Docker-to-Production MySQL Connectivity</h3>
    
    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Quick Fix (Recommended for Development - 30 minutes)</h4>
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: var(--spacing-small); border-left: 4px solid #1976d2;">Add <code>network_mode: host</code> to the web-dev service in docker-compose.yml to allow Docker containers to access the host network directly.</p>
    
    <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid #1976d2; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <strong>File</strong>: docker-compose.yml (web-dev service, around line 54-60)<br/>
        <strong>Change</strong>: Add this line after <code>container_name: comserv-web-dev</code>:
        <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;">  web-dev:
    build:
      context: ./Comserv
      dockerfile: Dockerfile
    container_name: comserv-web-dev
    network_mode: host                    # ← ADD THIS LINE
    restart: unless-stopped
    environment:</pre>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Why this works</strong>: The container will use the host's network stack and DNS, allowing it to reach 192.168.1.198 directly.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Trade-offs</strong>:</p>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>✅ Simple one-line fix</li>
            <li>✅ Immediate connectivity to production MySQL</li>
            <li>❌ Loses Docker network isolation</li>
            <li>❌ Not recommended for production</li>
            <li>❌ May cause port conflicts if host services use same ports</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>After making this change</strong>:</p>
        <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;">docker compose down
docker compose up -d web-dev
curl -I http://localhost:3000    # Should still work
docker logs comserv-web-dev      # Check if MySQL connection succeeds</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Long-term Solution (Recommended for Production - Phase 1)</h4>
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Implement Zerotier or Tailscale mesh VPN networking (already referenced in db_config.json). This is the approach recommended for multi-cloud, Kubernetes-ready deployments.</p>
    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
        <li>Install Zerotier client in Dockerfile</li>
        <li>Update environment to use ZeroTier virtual IP for database</li>
        <li>Works across local, on-site, and off-site networks</li>
        <li>Part of Phase 1 migration plan</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="phase-details" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase Details & Deliverables</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-100">
                <h2 id="phase-0.5" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 0.5: CI/CD Readiness Assessment & DBI Security Fix</h2>

                <div style="background-color: #e8f5e9; border-left: 4px solid #4caf50; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: #2e7d32; font-family: var(--header-font);">✅ GOOD NEWS: RemoteDB.pm Configuration System is PRODUCTION-READY</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Status (December 2025)</strong>: Code review confirms RemoteDB.pm already implements the complete K8s-ready configuration cascade. See <a href="/Documentation/system/PHASE_0_KUBERNETES_READINESS_PLAN">Phase0KubernetesReadinessPlan.tt</a> for detailed findings.</p>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>What Works</strong>:</p>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin: 5px 0;">
                        <li>K8s Secrets loading (lines 91-151)</li>
                        <li>Environment variable override pattern COMSERV_DB_* (lines 153-201)</li>
                        <li>db_config.json fallback (lines 203-224)</li>
                        <li>DBI connection establishment with driver fallback (lines 309-400)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>What Needs Work</strong>: Admin setup wizard for graceful error handling when no configuration found (currently dies at line 87)</p>
                </div>

                <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <h3 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);"> CRITICAL: DBI Security Errors - Fix Before Push</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Status</strong>: 8 commits pending push to main branch. Focus: Resolve DBI credential exposures in .env.example, docker-compose.dev.yml, and db_config.json handling. Pipeline exists but requires Secrets config.</p>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Risk Level</strong>: HIGH if pushed as-is. Credential leaks could expose DB access.</p>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Estimated Time to Resolve</strong>: 1-2 hours.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Current Git Status</h3>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>Staged for commit (9 files):   Comserv/root/Documentation/config/scan_state.json
   Comserv/root/Documentation/environment/*.tt (5 new files)
   Comserv/root/admin/documentation/manage_config.tt
   Documentation.pm
   root/templates/admin/schema_comparison.tt (DELETED - OK)Unstaged changes (Fix before staging):
    .dockerignore - review
    .env.example - DBI creds exposed (MUST FIX)
    Comserv/docker-compose.dev.yml - DBI creds exposed (MUST FIX)
    Controller/Documentation.pm - modified
    Controller/Documentation/ScanMethods.pm - modified
    Comserv/root/Documentation/config/documentation_config.json - modified
    Comserv/root/Documentation/system/DOCKER_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_STRATEGY.tt - modified
    Comserv/root/admin/documentation/*.tt (3 files) - modifiedCurrent branch: main
Commits ahead of origin/main: 8
                    </code></pre>
                    </div>                <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">DBI Security Issues & Fixes (2025-11-16 Audit)</h3>

                <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font);"> CRITICAL: DBI Credential Exposures</h4>

                <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Issue</th>
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Location</th>
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Risk</th>
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Fix</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Hardcoded DB Password</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Comserv/docker-compose.dev.yml (line 18)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;"><strong>CRITICAL</strong> - In git history</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Replace defaults with ${DB_PASS} (no value); use .env for local</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Example DBI Exposed</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">.env.example (DB_PASSWORD, etc.)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;"><strong>HIGH</strong> - Public repo exposure</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Use placeholders: DB_PASSWORD=your_db_password_here</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>db_config.json Handling</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">App startup (import logic)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;"><strong>HIGH</strong> - File-based creds</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Import to K8s Secrets on startup; delete file. Use Zerotier for new machines</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <h4 style="color: #4caf50; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);"> DBI Migration & Zerotier Integration</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Process</strong>: On container init, check for db_config.json; if present, parse and create K8s Secret (e.g., kubectl create secret generic dbi-secrets --from-literal=conn1='{"host":"db.zerotier","user":"...","pass":"..."}'). Mount Secret as env var or file in pods.</li>
                    <li><strong>New/Off-Site Machines</strong>: Install Zerotier client (one-command join). DB host resolves via Zerotier DNS (e.g., db-server.local.zerotier to 10.147.1.100). No json needed; pull from shared Secret or generate via admin UI.</li>
                    <li><strong>Why Zerotier?</strong>: Simple setup, zero-config VPN, built-in DNS for virtual IPs. Handles local/off-site seamlessly without firewall changes. Alternative: Tailscale for easier auth.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Step-by-Step: Fix DBI Security & Safe Push</h3>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">STEP 1: Create Kubernetes Secrets (One-time setup)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Create Secrets from existing db_config.json:</strong></p>
                    <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Create K8s Secret from db_config.json
kubectl create secret generic dbi-secrets --from-file=config=db_config.json -n default

# OR create from individual values
kubectl create secret generic dbi-secrets \
  --from-literal=db_host=db-server.local.zerotier \
  --from-literal=db_user=your_username \
  --from-literal=db_password=your_password \
  -n default

# Verify secret was created
kubectl get secrets
kubectl describe secret dbi-secrets</pre>
                    </div>                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">STEP 2: Mount Secrets in Application (Kubernetes)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">In Kubernetes deployment manifests, mount the dbi-secrets Secret as environment variables or volume:</p>
                    <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Option 1: Mount as environment variables (recommended)
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: comserv-app
spec:
  containers:
  - name: comserv
    image: ghcr.io/[org]/comserv:latest
    env:
    - name: DB_HOST
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          name: dbi-secrets
          key: db_host
    - name: DB_USER
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          name: dbi-secrets
          key: db_user
    - name: DB_PASSWORD
      valueFrom:
        secretKeyRef:
          name: dbi-secrets
          key: db_password

# Option 2: Mount as volume (for json config)
volumes:
- name: dbi-secrets
  secret:
    secretName: dbi-secrets
containers:
- volumeMounts:
  - name: dbi-secrets
    mountPath: /etc/secrets/dbi
    readOnly: true</pre>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>In application code (Perl):</strong></p>
                    <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Retrieve from environment (K8s Secret mounted as env vars)
my $db_host = $ENV{DB_HOST} || 'localhost';
my $db_user = $ENV{DB_USER} || 'default_user';
my $db_pass = $ENV{DB_PASSWORD} || '';

# OR read from mounted volume (if using volume mount)
open my $fh, '<', '/etc/secrets/dbi/db_password' or die "Cannot read Secret: $!";
my $db_pass = <$fh>;
close $fh;</pre>
                    </div>

                <h4 style="color: #4caf50; font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium);"> Testing Docker-Entrypoint Fallback (Non-K8s Environments)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Test File Created</strong>: <code>t/docker-entrypoint_non_k8s.t</code></p>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Purpose</strong>: Validates docker-entrypoint.sh behavior when kubectl is unavailable (non-Kubernetes environment). Ensures db_config.json is preserved and used directly as fallback.</p>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Test Coverage</strong>:</p>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                        <li>Verifies test db_config.json creation</li>
                        <li>Validates kubectl unavailable fallback message output</li>
                        <li>Confirms db_config.json is preserved (NOT deleted)</li>
                        <li>Ensures script exits without fatal kubectl-related errors</li>
                        <li>Validates fallback message indicates direct file usage</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Run Test</strong>: <code>perl -t t/docker-entrypoint_non_k8s.t</code></p>
                </div>                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">STEP 3: Configure Zerotier for Database Access (One-Time, 20 minutes)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Prerequisites</strong>: DB server must be reachable via Zerotier virtual IP (already configured per db_config.json references).</p>
                    <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                        <li><strong>For new/off-site machines</strong>: Install Zerotier client
                            <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;">curl -s https://install.zerotier.com | sudo bash
sudo zerotier-cli join [your-network-id]</pre>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Update K8s Secret</strong> with Zerotier DNS or virtual IP:
                            <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Update secret with Zerotier DB host
kubectl patch secret dbi-secrets -p '{"data":{"db_host":"'$(echo -n 'db-server.local.zerotier' | base64)'"}}'</pre>
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Test connectivity</strong>: Verify K8s pod can resolve DB host
                            <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;">kubectl run -it --rm debug --image=busybox -- nslookup db-server.local.zerotier</pre>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">STEP 4: Configure Database Connection for Docker (CRITICAL - 10 minutes)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border: 2px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>⚠️ IMPORTANT</strong>: Docker containers require explicit database connection configuration. See the "Database Connection Setup & Container Startup" section above for detailed instructions.</p>
                    
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>Quick Setup:</strong></p>
                    <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># 1. Create .env file with database credentials
cat > .env << 'EOF'
DB_HOST=192.168.1.198
DB_PORT=3306
DB_NAME=ency
DB_USER=shanta_forager
DB_PASS=your_actual_password_here
DB_HOST_PROD=192.168.1.198
DB_PORT_PROD=3306
DB_NAME_PROD=ency
DB_USER_PROD=shanta_forager
DB_PASS_PROD=your_actual_password_here
EOF
chmod 600 .env

# 2. Build containers (Docker v2 uses 'docker compose' not 'docker-compose')
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml build
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build

# 3. Start containers
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d    # Port 3000
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d   # Port 5000

# 4. Verify database connectivity
docker exec -it comserv-web-dev bash -c "mysql -h \$DB_HOST -P \$DB_PORT -u \$DB_USER -p\$DB_PASS -e 'SELECT 1;'"

# 5. Check application logs
docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs | grep -i "dbi\|database"
</pre>
                    
                    <p style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>⚠️ CRITICAL</strong>: The .env file contains passwords - never commit it to git! It's already in .gitignore.</p>
                </div>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">STEP 5: Verify No Credentials in Git & Push (5 minutes)</h4>
                <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Before committing, verify no credentials are exposed:</strong></p>
                    <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;"># Check for common credential patterns
git diff --cached | grep -iE "(password|secret|api_key|db_pass)" || echo "✅ No credentials found"

# Verify .env is not staged (should be ignored)
git status | grep .env && echo "❌ ERROR: .env file is staged!" || echo "✅ .env properly ignored"

# Review staged files
git diff --cached --stat

# Commit safely (using Docker v2 compose command syntax)
git commit -m "Phase 0.5 complete: DBI moved to Kubernetes Secrets, Docker v2 database setup documented"
git push origin main</pre>
                    <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 10px;"><strong>After push:</strong></p>
                    <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                        <li>Monitor GitHub Actions for build success</li>
                        <li>Secrets remain secure in K8s (not in git history)</li>
                        <li>Database credentials stored locally in .env (never committed)</li>
                        <li>Containers should connect successfully to production MySQL via host network</li>
                    </ul>
                    </div>                <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Configure GitHub Secrets for DBI</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); background-color: #e3f2fd; padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid #1976d2;"><strong>Note</strong>: Add DBI-related secrets post-push.</p>
                <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Secret Name</th>
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Value</th>
                        <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Used By</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">DBI_SECRET_JSON</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Base64-encoded db_config.json for init import</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Workflows 03/04 (decode and create Secret)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <!-- Existing secrets like STAGING_HOST, etc., omitted for brevity -->
                </table>
                
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Remaining phases details truncated for focus on current phase; expand as needed in future updates -->
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="cicd-checklist" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">CI/CD-ready Containerization Checklist</h2>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>PSGI entrypoint</strong>: Ensure script/comserv_server.psgi exists and returns Comserv->psgi_app.</li>
            <li><strong>Unified server</strong>: Run Starman everywhere via supervisor.</li>
            <li><strong>Entrypoint scripts</strong>: docker-entrypoint.sh handles DBI import to Secrets.</li>
            <li><strong>Dockerfile dependencies</strong>: Install Perl deps; include script/, lib/, root/.</li>
            <li><strong>Compose uses images</strong>: Reference GHCR images via .env.</li>
            <li><strong>Environment</strong>: Use Secrets for DBI; Zerotier for host resolution.</li>
            <li><strong>Config and volumes</strong>: Mount Secrets as files/envs; no json persistence.</li>
            <li><strong>Healthchecks</strong>: /health endpoint for compose/K8s.</li>
            <li><strong>Networking</strong>: Publish ports; use Zerotier IPs.</li>
            <li><strong>CI build/push</strong>: Build and push to GHCR.</li>
            <li><strong>Server deploy</strong>: Pull and up via compose.</li>
            <li><strong>Kubernetes readiness</strong>: Mount dbi-secrets in deployments.</li>
        </ol>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Docker Setup Guide -->
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="docker-setup" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Docker/PyCharm/GitHub Setup Guide</h2>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Local Development Environment Setup</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This guide walks you through setting up Docker locally with PyCharm integration and GitHub for development.</p>
        
        <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h4>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Docker Desktop installed and running</li>
            <li>PyCharm IDE (Community or Professional)</li>
            <li>Git installed locally</li>
            <li>GitHub account with repository access</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Step 1: Clone Repository</h4>
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>git clone https://github.com/your-org/comserv.git
cd comserv
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your local database credentials
nano .env</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Step 2: Build and Start Docker Containers</h4>
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>docker compose build
docker compose up -d web-dev
docker compose logs web-dev  # Check startup logs</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Step 3: Configure PyCharm Docker Integration</h4>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Open PyCharm settings: <strong>Preferences → Project → Python Interpreter</strong></li>
            <li>Click the gear icon and select <strong>Add</strong></li>
            <li>Choose <strong>Docker Compose</strong></li>
            <li>Select docker-compose.yml and service: <strong>web-dev</strong></li>
            <li>Click <strong>OK</strong> to set as project interpreter</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 15px;">Step 4: Test Your Setup</h4>
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>curl http://localhost:3000  # Should return HTML
docker compose exec web-dev perl -v  # Check Perl installation</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Developer Workflow Evolution -->
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="workflow" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Developer Workflow Evolution</h2>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Current Workflow (Manual)</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Phase 0</strong>: Manual SSH and git pull on production server. Limited to single developer. No CI/CD automation.</p>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 15px;">Phase 1-2: Local Docker Development</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Workflow</strong>:</p>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Developer edits code locally (mounted in container via volumes)</li>
            <li>Tests in containerized environment matching production</li>
            <li>Commits and pushes to GitHub</li>
            <li>Manual deployment to testing server</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 15px;">Phase 3-5: CI/CD Pipeline Integration</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Workflow</strong>:</p>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Developer pushes to GitHub feature branch (future)</li>
            <li>GitHub Actions automatically builds and tests</li>
            <li>On merge to main, automatically pushes to container registry (GHCR)</li>
            <li>Kubernetes auto-pulls latest image</li>
            <li>Zero-downtime rolling update</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 15px;">Phase 6-7: Full Kubernetes Automation</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Workflow</strong>: Same as Phase 3-5 but with:</p>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>Automatic horizontal pod scaling based on load</li>
            <li>Self-healing containers and nodes</li>
            <li>Cross-datacenter/multi-cloud deployment support</li>
            <li>Advanced monitoring and alerting</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Success Metrics & Timeline -->
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="metrics" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Success Metrics & Timeline</h2>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Key Success Metrics</h3>
        
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Metric</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Current</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Target (Phase 7)</strong></th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Deployment Time</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">15-30 minutes (manual)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">&lt;5 minutes (automated)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Downtime per Deploy</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">5-10 minutes</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">0 minutes (zero-downtime)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Rollback Time</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">30+ minutes (manual recovery)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">&lt;1 minute (one-click)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Development Environment Parity</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">70% match (manual setup)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">100% match (docker-compose)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Infra. Scalability</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Manual (1 server)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Auto-scaling (N+ servers)</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Project Timeline (4-6 months)</h3>
        
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>Month 1</strong>: Phase 0.5 (DBI Security) + Phase 1 (Local Docker)</li>
            <li><strong>Month 1-2</strong>: Phase 2 (All Components Containerized)</li>
            <li><strong>Month 2</strong>: Phase 3 (CI/CD Pipeline) + Phase 4 (Testing Environment)</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3</strong>: Phase 5 (Production Docker Deployment)</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3-4</strong>: Phase 6 (Single-Node Kubernetes)</li>
            <li><strong>Month 4-6</strong>: Phase 7 (Multi-Node Kubernetes Cluster)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="docker-updates" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Updating Docker Containers When Modified</h2>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">When you modify Docker images, configuration files, or code within containers, you need to rebuild and restart the containers to apply changes. This section provides step-by-step guidance for different modification scenarios.</p>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Quick Reference: When to Rebuild</h3>
        
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <tr style="background-color: var(--light-color);">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Modification Type</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Action Required</strong></th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Restart Required</strong></th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Code files (lib/, root/, script/)</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Usually NO rebuild needed (if mounted as volumes)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;">⚠️ Restart container to reload</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Dockerfile changes</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">REBUILD image</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">✅ YES - must recreate</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>docker-compose.yml changes</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No rebuild needed</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">✅ YES - recreate containers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background-color: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Environment variables (.env)</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No rebuild needed</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #d32f2f;">✅ YES - restart to apply</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Configuration files (config/)</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Usually NO rebuild needed (if mounted)</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;">⚠️ Maybe - depends on file change</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Scenario 1: Code Changes Only (lib/, root/, script/)</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Use Case</strong>: You modified Perl code or template files. These are typically mounted as volumes in docker-compose.yml.</p>
        
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Step 1: Verify your changes are saved
git status

# Step 2: Restart the container to reload code
docker compose restart web-dev

# Step 3: Check logs for any startup errors
docker compose logs web-dev

# Step 4: Test the application
curl http://localhost:3000</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Why this works</strong>: Code is mounted as a volume, so the running container immediately sees the updated files. Restarting forces the Perl process to reload modules.</p>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>If changes don't appear</strong>: The app may cache compiled modules in memory. A full rebuild may be needed:
        <pre style="background:#f7f7f7; padding:8px; white-space:pre-wrap; color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace;">docker compose down
docker compose up -d web-dev</pre>
        </p>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Scenario 2: Dockerfile Modified (Dependencies, Base Image, etc.)</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Use Case</strong>: You updated the Dockerfile to install new Perl modules, change the base image, or modify build steps.</p>
        
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Step 1: Review Dockerfile changes
git diff Dockerfile

# Step 2: Stop and remove old containers
docker compose down

# Step 3: Rebuild the image (forces fresh build)
docker buildx build --no-cache --load -t comserv:latest ./Comserv

# Step 4: Start the new container
docker compose up -d web-dev

# Step 5: Verify the build succeeded
docker compose logs web-dev | grep -i "error\|failed" || echo "✅ Build succeeded"

# Step 6: Test the application
curl http://localhost:3000</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Important flags</strong>:</p>
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><code>--no-cache</code>: Rebuilds every layer (don't use cached layers from previous builds)</li>
            <li><code>-d</code>: Detach mode (run in background)</li>
            <li>Omit <code>--no-cache</code> for faster builds if layers haven't changed significantly</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Scenario 3: docker-compose.yml Modified (Ports, Volumes, Env Vars)</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Use Case</strong>: You changed environment variables, port mappings, volume mounts, or service definitions in docker-compose.yml.</p>
        
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Step 1: Review compose changes
git diff docker-compose.yml

# Step 2: Validate syntax
docker compose config > /dev/null && echo "✅ Valid" || echo "❌ Invalid syntax"

# Step 3: Stop and remove containers (but keep volumes)
docker compose down

# Step 4: Restart with new configuration
docker compose up -d web-dev

# Step 5: Check that services started correctly
docker compose ps

# Step 6: Verify in logs
docker compose logs web-dev</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Key differences from Dockerfile changes</strong>:
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li>✅ No rebuild needed (use existing image)</li>
            <li>✅ Faster than full rebuild</li>
            <li>⚠️ May need to recreate containers to apply new port/volume mappings</li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Scenario 4: Complete Clean Rebuild (Nuclear Option)</h3>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Use Case</strong>: Multiple changes across Dockerfile, compose file, and code. You want a guaranteed clean state.</p>
        
        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>⚠️ WARNING</strong>: This removes all containers and images. Make sure you don't have unsaved data in volumes.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Step 1: Backup any important data
docker compose logs web-dev > backup_logs.txt

# Step 2: Stop all containers
docker compose down

# Step 3: Remove images (optional but thorough)
docker compose down --rmi all

# Step 4: Clean up any unused Docker resources
docker system prune -f

# Step 5: Rebuild everything from scratch
docker compose build --no-cache

# Step 6: Start fresh
docker compose up -d

# Step 7: Verify
docker compose ps
docker compose logs</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Troubleshooting: Container Won't Start After Changes</h3>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);"><strong>Problem 1: Port Already in Use</strong></h4>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Error: "bind: address already in use"
# Solution: Find and stop the process using the port
lsof -i :3000
kill -9 &lt;PID&gt;

# Or just remove all containers
docker compose down</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-top: 15px;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);"><strong>Problem 2: Out of Disk Space</strong></h4>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Error: "no space left on device"
# Solution: Clean up Docker images and containers
docker system prune -a -f
docker volume prune -f

# Check remaining space
docker system df</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-top: 15px;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);"><strong>Problem 3: Syntax Errors in Dockerfile or Compose</strong></h4>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Test docker-compose syntax
docker compose config

# Test Dockerfile with Hadolint (if installed)
hadolint Dockerfile

# Review recent changes
git diff Dockerfile
git diff docker-compose.yml</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-top: 15px;">
            <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);"><strong>Problem 4: Application Crashes on Startup</strong></h4>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code># Check detailed logs
docker compose logs web-dev --tail 100

# Check if database is accessible
docker compose exec web-dev mysql -h &lt;host&gt; -u &lt;user&gt; -p -e "SELECT 1;"

# Verify environment variables are set
docker compose exec web-dev env | grep COMSERV</code></pre>
        </div>
        
        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Best Practices for Container Updates</h3>
        
        <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
            <li><strong>Test locally first</strong>: Always test changes on your development machine before pushing to production.</li>
            <li><strong>Use version tags</strong>: When pushing to registry (GHCR), use specific version tags (v1.2.3) not just "latest".</li>
            <li><strong>Keep Dockerfile clean</strong>: Minimize layers, use multi-stage builds for smaller images.</li>
            <li><strong>Document changes</strong>: Update this file and commit messages when modifying Docker configuration.</li>
            <li><strong>Monitor logs</strong>: Always check logs after starting containers to catch startup errors early.</li>
            <li><strong>Use .dockerignore</strong>: Similar to .gitignore, prevents unnecessary files from being copied into images.</li>
            <li><strong>Security scanning</strong>: Periodically scan images for vulnerabilities: <code>docker scan &lt;image&gt;</code></li>
        </ul>
        
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-top: 15px;"><a href="#nav-menu" style="color: var(--link-color);">↑ Back to Navigation</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-100">
        <h2 id="next-steps" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Next Steps</h2>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Immediate Actions</h3>
        <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
